fields: I'm Suzukaze Aoba. Nice to meet you.
I'm Suzukaze Aoba. Nice to meet you.
This is a company, so no kids allowed.
I'll be working at Eagle Jump starting today. I am Suzukaze Aoba.
Oh, you were a new employee? I'm sorry about that.
I'm sorry as well. My name is Suzukaze Aoba.
Suzukaze... Oh, I have. We're on the same team.
I'm Toyama Rin. I'm an AD. It's nice to meet you.
So... You must be busy being an AD.
I see it quite often on the TV, but there are so many intricate tasks, and they look so busy.
Oh, my AD doesn't stand for "assistant director."
So my job is to manage all the artwork.
Oh, would you like something to drink?
I'm so glad she seems nice.
I'm going to be a professional starting today.
She's our new employee. Suzukaze Aoba-san.
Oh, this is mine, but do you want it?
You have a mature taste. You drink coffee black?
I'm an adult. This is no big deal.
Wow, you're a high school grad? That's rare.
But you don't even look like a high schooler.
What about you? How old are you?
Oh, you know it? That's the first game I was involved in.
What? I was totally into it in elementary school.
That's how I found out about this company...
D-D-Don't tell me... you're thir I'm not that old!
I'm twenty-five. I joined after high school, too.
Don't worry about it. By the way.
We're the same age! Good girl.
I'm meeting with the people who made the game I loved as a child.
I especially loved the character design.
My. She's Yagami Ko who did the character designs for Fairies Story.
Well that earned me respect easy.
She will be your manager starting today, so I hope you two get along.
I think this is a good pose.
Please Hold Your Card Up To The Circle Open
H-Hello! I'm Suzukaze Aoba. I'm starting today.
Takimoto Hifumi. Nice to meet you.
Are you also on the character team?
What? Why is there a cat here?
You came all the way here?
Are you the new employee, Suzukaze Aoba-kun?
I'm Hazuki Shizuku, the director of the game this team is making.
Okay. It's nice to meet you.
He's Mozuku. I bring him in sometime.
If I leave him at home all the time, he gets bored and messes up the house.
Hazuki-san, I've been looking for you.
Oh, Umiko-kun. What do you need?
You're very late for the meeting.
Oh, oopsy. Let's not look so upset.
I don't know anything besides drawing.
Then do chapter one of this book.
Excuse me, Hifumi-senpai. Could I ask you a question?
But I think I've already figured it out.
I got a message from Aoba.
Suzukaze-san, you want to go out for lunch?
Hifumi-senpai doesn't usually go out to lunch.
I hope you'll join us next time.
Aoba, wanna go out for lunch? Where is she?
I'm Ijima Yun on the character team. She and I joined the same year.
I'm Shinoda Hajime on the motion team. Nice to...
I can't! It's my first time having a kouhai.
Please don't worry. You're my senpai. Shinoda-senpai.
That gives me goosebumps, so just call me Hajime.
Hajime-san, then. You can just call me Aoba.
Nice to meet you, Aoba... san.
She was asking me to invite you in private messaging earlier.
You're nervous because she's your first kouhai, right?
Isn't she your first kouhai, too?
You were worried about her when she was trying to talk to Hifumi-senpai earlier, too.
All right! Let's get this done!
But first, I need to use the restroom.
Bathroom, bathroom... When you gotta go, you gotta
I went to use the restroom, but I didn't have my ID card, so I couldn't open the office door.
Oh, right. The bathroom is outside the office.
Without your ID card, you can't get into the office, but we also can't track your time.
What is the management thinking, forgetting to give it to you.
Ko-chan, did you already take Aoba-chan's ID card picture?
Hey. I asked you to do it this morning.
Stand in front of the wall.
You know, you can wear whatever you want here, but why are you in your school uniform?
Oh, please. This isn't a school uniform. This is a suit.
Then at least learn how to wear a suit properly.
I heard what you were thinking just now!
Hajime, can I borrow your light?
Look forward to the finished product.
I see. You couldn't come back in.
Yeah. I didn't know what to do, and I was about to cry.
You really had it rough. Want to relax with some snacks?
Yeah. I'm trying to learn as fast as possible, so I can help out.
What's the release date of the game we're making right now?
It's in six months. The rumor is, we're going to get super busy soon. What?
You won't be able to go home for a while.
But Yagami-san was already sleeping here.
Is it because she's the leader?
I think it's accurate to say she lives here.
She's incredible. She does several times more work than everyone else.
Though she has some personality problems.
Aoba, thanks for waiting. Here's your ID card.
Now I really feel like an official employee.
It's fine to take breaks, but you guys are still clocked in, so make sure you get back to work soon.
So how far have you gotten, Aoba?
I'll send you some work soon, then, so be ready.
You'll learn the small things through experience.
I'm glad she seems to be a fast learner. She might turn out to be reliable.
But first, I need to use the restroom.
Yagami-san, you're not staying here tonight?
I wouldn't last if I stayed overnight every night.
Rin would get mad at me, too.
She gets mad a lot sometimes.
I... I forgot to ask you something important.
What's the title of the new video game we're making?
We forgot to tell her, too.
We're making the third installment of Fairies Story.
That's the video game that made me want to be a character designer!
I'll do my best! Thank you for having me!
Aocchi, is a video game company really busy?
I don't know, Nenecchi. But there was someone who slept at work.
Did you run into someone sleeping in her underwear?
Just kidding. No adult does that.
Don't be a bad example to other workers.
I got the new wand from Moon Ranger!
There are twenty different quotes in this thing.
See this? When you swing it...
Ow. Oh, no! I'm sorry, Yun!
Why're you getting so carried away at this time of morning?
I'm sorry. I got carried away.
I'm getting the urge to swing it around, too.
Motion Team Effect Team A little lonely on the diagram
Stop, I can't work with you around me.
I'm so sorry! I'm playing with your cat.
I don't care. Mozuku's at fault for interrupting your work.
In fact, you could discipline me as his owner, too.
Come on, don't get in her way, Mozuku.
Tomorrow (4/10) is Aoba's welcome party! Don't Overeat or Drink Too Much!! Aoba-chan.
What are you doing for lunch?
We're gonna go buy boxed lunches.
I'm almost done with this part, so I'm going to finish up.
You should at least snack on this.
I shall repay you one day!
You can buy me lunch sometime.
N-No. I was just wondering what you did for lunch.
I ate at home before coming here.
What? That's amazing. I don't have time for that.
Though I come a little before lunch...
I wanted to eat with Sojiro.
Wanna see his picture? Can I really?
Oh. You mentioned a boy's name, so I thought he was your boyfriend or something.
I can't feel relaxed around men.
Oh! I totally get it! I get a bit nervous, too.
I don't really speak from experience.
I'm sorry. I was talking about my fantasy world, too.
Wow! He's so cute! Isn't he?
Not really. He's always hiding in his hole.
But... We've gotten close to where I can touch him.
No. Well... I look so weird.
Not at all! Your smile is so cute!
You'd be much more approachable like that.
Then don't look at me. Look at Sojiro-kun.
Oh, I wanted to work on my training.
Taking breaks is part of the job.
I feel kind of bad. Yun-san gave me her snack, too.
I'll take you out to eat sometime, too!
I can't let the newbie take me out!
When you're busy, you should buy something before coming in.
Thank you so much. I'll enjoy it.
Wow, it's already so late! I have to eat fast.
I'm home. Sojiro, do you like it when I smile?
Yeah. I got in a fight with Sojiro. A fight?
I don't think Sojiro likes my smile.
How far are you in the textbook?
Oh, here. I'm at this part right now.
Cool. Let's give you a project.
Real work. You're gonna work on your first project.
This is Knight-kun, the protagonist of Fairies Story 3.
He looks great no matter how much I look at him.
But this town's kind of lonely with no one around.
That's right. Your first job is to make this city lively.
I already did the designs, so you just model them in 3D.
By the way, you call characters you don't control "NPCs."
The characters you can control are "PCs."
All the NPCs in this town are done, so you can look at them as reference.
So many cat ears! So cute!
It's a cat town. Hifumin did a great job here.
Hifumi-senpai! I'll do my best, too!
You got your first project, Aoba-chan?
Watching you reminds me of when I was just starting out.
Though she hasn't messed up as much.
I didn't mess up too much, either.
I just sometimes spilled tea or went to the wrong company.
It's my second year now, though!
So don't expect me messing up anymore.
No! I'll go grab a towel!
I see! So that's how that goes.
Aoba! It's almost time for the party.
How do I do this part?
It's time. Don't make everyone wait.
Well, then. Let's get started with the welcome party for Suzukaze Aoba-chan.
The company's paying for it today!
Let's all eat and drink like crazy!
Hey, don't grab all the meat!
What was that? It's so spicy.
Spicy takoyaki, Russian roulette style. And you lost!
Aoba-chan, is this your first time at a drinking party?
After all, you're not of drinking age yet.
I figured I'd drop by. Suzukaze-kun, how is it?
I heard. You were already assigned a project?
Yes, but I haven't made much progress with it.
It's still your first day on the project.
Working on a 3D project after just one week might be too soon, Yagami.
Well, she was working through the textbook pretty fast, so I figured...
Why can't you be more straightforward?
Just say you were genuinely impressed.
Suzukaze-kun. Yagami isn't very straightforward and is actually a bit sensitive, so be gentle with her.
Please just go home already! This is a party for the character team!
I'm on the motion team, you know...
Don't try to make things complicated!
Our staff can be a little weird, but I hope you don't get too weirded out.
Not at all. I was a little apprehensive about joining the company, but I'm relieved that everyone's so nice.
Now, then. I'm going to go now.
Mozuku will get lonely without me.
What? Wh-Why would I have one?
But you look like you have one.
What? Wh-Why would I have one?
Why are you blushing like a little girl?
I work all the time and have no time for love!
I'll drink this. That's a stiff drink!
I jon't have a boyfwiend, eijer.
Aoba-shan! Newbiesh should be pouwing alcohol fer their senpai!
Thash not how ya pour beer for shumone! Watch and learn! Ko-chan!
See? This ish the besht in terms of both looks and tashte!
She drank too much despite being a lightweight.
Can I have this... Mori Musashi? Please. Mori Musashi (Mori Takezo)
How would you like it served?
We can serve on the rocks, water mix, or soda mix.
Hifumi-senpai, how do you want it?
It would be straight if I serve it as is.
Mori Takezo, straight. I'll bring it right out.
Wow, alcohol is expensive. Some go for 800 yen a glass.
I could buy a manga volume with that.
Um... May I have a sip?
Yay! The legal drinking age of  alcohol in Japan is twenty.
I-I-I'm sorry! B-B-But I haven't done anything yet!
Do you have anything else you'd like to order?
All right, then. Who's coming to the after party?
I need to take Yun home.
Let's go with the three of us!
I'm not trying alcohol anymore, so... Do they have juice here?
Hey! I'll have the Orange Blossom!
I didn't have any drinks, but I feel drunk.
Get this! Everyone at college treats me like a middle schooler!
But you look and act like a kid, so you can't blame them.
B-But I'm a working member of society and learning adult things.
Cool. Is that for Fairies Story 3?
That silence was just my wishful thinking.
Besides, I can't tell you what we're working on.
I'm sorry, I'll forget it. I'll forget what I heard.
I won't let you get arrested!
You drink alcohol so well, Hifumi-senpai.
I want to drink hot sake with some broiled stingray fin dipped with spicy mayonnaise.
That's the person I aspire to become.
I'd forgotten that my mom was out today.
Wait, I'm not a student anymore.
What happens if I'm late? Will I get in trouble?
It's great that you're feeling  more comfortable here, but...
As punishment, you're going to stay here in your underwear tonight.
Oh, could it be that you're late, too? What a coincidence.
Well, sometimes stuff  happens and you end up late.
W-Well, we're technically not late yet.
If we run from the station, we might make it on time.
Sorry to disappoint you, but with my endurance, I can only run for a minute.
So you can go on your own if you want.
Get Your Dream Body in Just 2 Months! Aoba-chan, are you good at sports?
When I was in school, I was always one of the last ones to finish.
People who run slow also usually run funny.
I'm super slow and always finished last, too.
People always tell me I run weird, too! I see.
Y-Yun-san! I'm sorry! I... can't run anymore!
You can't give up! Let's do our best and run until the end!
At this pace, we can make it on time!
What? It's rather empty in here today.
No one's called in sick yet, so they might be running a bit late.
Three people late? They all need a reality check.
I'll have to be a little strict with them.
Of course I can. How rude!
Wow, how nice of you to be walking in so leisurely.
It hasn't even been a month since you joined! You're not in school anymore!
Ko-chan, they got to the front of the building.
Aoba-chan tripped and fell, and we were helping her pick up her stuff, so that's why we're late.
So that's why your nose is red.
Wh-Why didn't you explain yourselves sooner? I made a terrible assumption.
You're always working so hard, so it's not that I actually think you mess around too much.
But I'm still your manager. Anyway, I'm sorry for what I said earlier.
I'll let it slide for today, but make sure all three of you submit a tardy form.
I tried something new and messed up.
Ko-chan, you should've asked what happened first.
Why did you both put down "overslept" as the reason for being late?
I can't let you off the hook with that.
What exactly is this? I spent too much time eating breakfast.
Breakfast was just so good today, so I...
Don't write emoticons on official documents!
Jeez! Why did I feel bad earlier?
It's pretty good for your first time.
However, it's lacking shadow and depth.
If you compare your character with Hifumin's, she doesn't stand out as much.
Also, her facial expression looks stiff. She's also a bit inconsistent.
B-But isn't this just a villager? People don't look at them that carefully.
I always look at NPCs carefully.
Why is my character moving so disgustingly?
I think Kii-chan should move more swiftly.
What? That's not how she should be.
She lives in a cave, you know?
Wait, all of them? This week?
Get me some more disgustingly awesome stuff.
Don't forget that you're getting this after me.
Mozuku. Even if you beg me, I won't feed you.
Mozuku-chan, it's clear that your begging has spoiled you.
Your selfish body speaks for itself.
So can you play with my body to your heart's content?
If you'd like... You can play with my body.
You prefer Mozuku's body over mine.
What a shame. You can use him anytime, so whenever you feel down, feel free to play with him.
Good night. It's late, so be careful going home.
Yagami-san. Can you take a look?
You need to think about which part of the character you want to highlight.
Aoba-chan. It's late, so you should go home now.
It's much better, but it still looks a little stiff.
I'll give you the whole day today, so do another retake.
It's true that compared to Hifumi-senpai's, I may still have a long way to go.
Looks like Yagami-san's being pretty strict.
I was confident it would pass this time.
I like your character, at least.
Can I take a quick look?
I think it's great for a first model.
Oh, but I'm still not satisfied with a lot of parts.
Don't worry about delays. It's already late today, so let's go home.
Do you live on your own?
No, I live with my parents.
Then they must be worried with you coming home late every night.
Yeah. I called my mom earlier, and she told me that staying up late is bad for my skin.
So she's not that worried about your safety...
Is it fun creating an NPC?
But I never knew it was so difficult.
Before, I just drew on my own, and it was done when I was happy, so it's my first time receiving so many critiques.
I see. That's what it means to make something professionally.
To be honest, what you turned in this morning...
It was good enough, but it got a retake?
I guess she didn't want you to be happy with just "good enough."
She has high hopes for you, you know.
I have to switch trains here, so good night.
She has high hopes for me?
Yeah. I'm near my house. I'm just getting home.
It's not even close to completion.
I'm having a hard time modeling a villager right now.
Yeah. Yagami-san's really strict about it.
I'm just modeling an adorable villager girl.
She'd be perfect for a florist.
She takes care of her parents, is responsible, energetic, and...
What? The dreamer type is more up in the clouds, but the responsible type is more tough and sincere.
Hello? This is Nenecchi. Can you hear me?
Hey! Put on a skirt, please.
Yagami-san, you should act more like a lady when you sleep.
Um, I'm sorry it's been so delayed.
I just finished up the villager model.
Yeah. It's good. It's much better.
I'm satisfied with this character, but if I make another one from scratch, I think I can do much better.
Also, I spent too long on it.
This one took more than a week, but let's try making one in three days next.
Ultimately, I need you making one a day. What?
Is this what Hifumi-senpai was talking about when she said we'll have to live here?
Well, you can leave when you're done.
I don't want to sleep in my underwear.
I'm talking about when you sleep!
Sorry for hanging up so abruptly last night.
I just wanted to hear your voice.
Good work getting one villager done.
Thank you. I didn't know you spend time making every villager.
You'll be making way more, too.
You have another hundred or so to go.
What? Can I really get that done? Next time: "The First... Paycheck..."
Next Time "The First... Paycheck..." You have to, even if you can't!
She's a bit too tall compared to  the other characters, so can you make her shorter?
It's already late today, though, so you can finish up tomorrow.
But, Aoba-chan, compared to before, you were much faster.
Not at all. I'm still really slow.
Isn't it a lot of work bringing  Mozuku-chan to work every day?
Yeah, he is a bit heavy.
Though that helps me gain some muscles.
You may need to go on a bit of diet.
It's been almost a month since you joined.
What do you think? Are you getting used to the job?
Not at all. I still get asked to do a lot of retakes.
Your smile was just really good, so I had to.
You had to? That's not a good reason.
What are you working on right now?
Oh. I'm almost done with the third villager.
So you've been fixing that one up?
And the retakes weigh on me a lot, but I can tell it gets better every time I make the changes.
And when Yagami-san gives me the okay, it's the best feeling in the world.
I don't know if I should be saying this.
What is it? You can tell me everything. I'll keep it off the record.
I don't think it's good for her to sleep in her underwear.
But when I see her working, and the more I work with her, I realize she's simply incredible.
So she's my role model and an inspiration.
I missed the last train. Here, I bought drinks.
You're lucky it was me who found you.
I'm the only one here anyway, so why don't you take off your pants?
Even if it's just you, I couldn't  possibly take my pants off at work!
I think you have a lot of knots from sleeping here.
I go home every other day.
I think you should be going home every day!
Sleeping here together feels like we have a deadline coming up.
It's going to get more lively here soon.
It's our job to prevent that, you know?
I wonder if the game will sell.
I only care about releasing a product I'm proud of.
Do you have butterflies in your stomach since it's your first project as the AD?
Oftentimes I think you would've made a better AD.
You make the personality of the game after all.
It's thanks to your management that I get to focus on all my work.
And backgrounds are just as important in a video game.
Besides, with my personality, no one would follow me.
Why am I being so negative?
You can't show this side of you to anyone.
Anyway, I don't know if it'll sell well, but I think it's becoming a good game.
Well, to be honest, if our newbie, Aoba, is enjoying  herself working on it, we'll be fine.
She wouldn't enjoy working on a boring game.
Yeah, I'm glad Aoba-chan's such a good girl.
But if she wants to be a designer,  I need her to be much more assertive.
I know. But if it were me, I'd find a character I like and
ask to design it, even if I got turned down.
But to be honest, I think she has her hands full with her villager project.
Maybe you can let her design  something easy once she finishes that.
Once she finishes all her villagers, I might give her a design project...
I wanted to get back to work, and I can't.
It's a big deal! This is why I hate 3D!
I already had coffee, so I'm gonna design.
Don't overwork yourself. I'm going to sleep.
I wonder if it really feels liberating.
You're lucky it was me who found you.
Please hold your card up to the circle Open
Jeez. Why do I have to hide?
I wonder if Yagami-san stayed the night again.
Good morning. Did you sleep here again
Hifumi-chan. Salary Statement Here you go.
Take a look at it later.
This is your first paycheck, isn't it?
Yeah! I've never worked part-time either, so it's literally my first.
So when you do direct deposit, you just get a statement?
Because when I hear salary, I had the idea of saying, "Ooh! I'm gonna be loaded this month!"
Or "I'm poor," depending on the weight of the envelope.
B-But... is it really okay for me to take this?
This is all I've done, and I've even received overtime.
You're staying late every night, so don't feel so reserved.
That's right. So you have to work really hard, so you can fully contribute to the company soon.
And once the company realizes your skills, you'll get a raise!
Hajime-san, did you get a raise?
What gave that away? Though it wasn't a lot.
You're just gonna spend it all on the toys for your desk.
I use them as references. Yagami-san uses them a lot, too.
You really like that, don't you? Even though it's useless.
What are you talking about? Its awesomeness alone makes it valuable.
It's important to work with a lot of energy, I suppose.
I even have a Western-style sword.
Aoba-chan, hold it. I dare you.
Wow, it's thin, but it's really heavy.
Isn't it? It's a slab of metal.
You get a raise once a year, so maybe you'll get paid more next year.
Do I get evaluated well if I produce quality work?
Since you're just starting out, you just  need to complete the work you're given.
on how much you've contributed to the team in addition to your own work.
By the way, the character team gets evaluated by your leader, Ko-chan, and myself, the AD.
But for now, just do what you think is helpful.
But you know, you guys have it hard with Yagami-san since she's strict about work.
You say it like it doesn't apply to you.
Yagami-san isn't the leader of the motion team.
Wait. Then why are you in this booth despite being part of the motion team?
I want to be with my own team, too. I'm sorry.
We ran out of space at the motion team booth.
But it's just one booth over.
By the way, do you already know how you're using your first paycheck?
Oh? I don't know. I hadn't thought that far ahead.
How did everyone here spend theirs?
If you buy a figure that you like, it'll be even more memorable!
I splurged a bit to buy from a good brand.
I wonder what you all would look good in.
Hazuki-san, what did you buy with your first paycheck?
It was so long ago, so I don't remember too well.
Oh. Then how old are you?
I stopped keeping track of my age after twenty, so...
I should've known I'd find you loitering around.
It's fine to take breaks, but what happened to the  documents I asked you to look over?
I'd forgotten. Let me finish taking my break.
If anyone's curious to find out Hazuki-san's age, I can be of assistance.
Shall we go, Umiko-kun? Time is of the essence, after all.
So what were we talking about?
That's right. What are you gonna do with it, Aoba-chan?
How did you use yours, Toyama-san?
What are you guys all talking about?
I was asking Toyama-san how she spent her first paycheck.
We had a day trip to a hot spring together.
Jeez, you don't have to get so mad over just a trip.
Just a trip? We picked the place and everything together.
Then do you remember where we went?
It must be a bit lonely that you're the only new hire this year.
But it doesn't bother me too much since I feel like we're all the same age.
What are you saying? We act more immature around you so we're more approachable.
Hifumi-senpai, do you have someone you joined with?
That's kinda sad that you guys got separated.
Not really. I don't talk much.
By the way, how'd you spend your first paycheck?
W-Well, saving up is nice, but I think doing something memorable is good, too.
Though some people will forget it anyway.
But you're right. I'll think of something.
I didn't ask out of jealousy.
But maybe I'll buy something on my way home, too.
Aoba-chan, you can take off now, too.
You should take the opportunity and leave early today.
I wonder what I should do.
The bath is ready, so you should get in.
I got my first paycheck today, so I bought a cake!
Rin. Hey, are you still mad?
No. I'm not mad at all.
I just completely forgot about the hot spring.
I don't care. Our very first trip together probably meant nothing to you anyway.
I'm just kidding. I'm sorry, Ko-chan. I'm really not mad.
I know. Let's go somewhere nice together right now.
I've always wanted to come to this spa.
Well, you were saying your stomach hurt from the responsibility as an AD.
Oh, it's better to heat up your stomach first.
Yeah, this upper arm feels kinda...
Aoba-chan, you bought a cake for your parents?
Yeah. My dad was in tears.
Every father's happy when their daughter does something nice.
But my mom ate it all while he was crying.
Yeah. I'm adding motions to her.
This is the idle motion. What do you think?
She's a cute model, so I think you should make it more cutesy.
I think she's curious about her.
So this is the conversation motion?
